## Encoding strategies and editorial policies

The following was referenced when creating a taxonomy. A separate file is desired for the taxonomy, 
which can be used to update as the project grows. While this is not an explicit published taxonomy, 
it is a way to assign meaning to items in the text that have meaning established elsewhere, which can 
be searched on at a later time. Notice Nested Items. This layout should be updated to reflect a more readable
structure.

                    <category xml:id="ph"><catDesc>philosophy</catDesc>
                        <category xml:id="Deleuze"><catDesc>Gilles Deleuze</catDesc></category>
                        <category xml:id="immanence"><catDesc>concept: GD Domain of Immanence </catDesc></category>
                        <category xml:id="Zizek"><catDesc>Slavoj Žižek, philosopher primarily from lecture material</catDesc></category>
                         <category xml:id="desire"><catDesc>concept: desire</catDesc></category>
                     </category>                
                     <category xml:id="ps"><catDesc>psychology</catDesc>
                        <category xml:id="bowlby"><catDesc>John Bowlby, British psychiatrist and psychoanalyst, child development and attachment theory</catDesc></category>
                         <category xml:id="growth"><catDesc>concept: growth, post-traumatic</catDesc></category>
                         <category xml:id="Lacan"><catDesc>Jacques Lacan, French psychoanalyst and psychiatrist </catDesc></category>
                        <category xml:id="consciousness"><catDesc>concept: unconscious, subconscious, conscious layer </catDesc></category>
                        <category xml:id="dream"><catDesc>concept: dream, dreaming </catDesc></category>
                     </category>
                        <category xml:id="bio"><catDesc>biology and physiology</catDesc>
                            <category xml:id="sleep"><catDesc>sleep processes</catDesc></category>
                            <category xml:id="sauna"><catDesc>sauna and health</catDesc></category>
                            <category xml:id="neuralplasticity"><catDesc> brain's ability to change and adapt in response to learning, experience, or injury</catDesc></category>
                            <category xml:id="mirrorneurons"><catDesc>neuroal mimicing behavior, in psychology explored by Daniel Siegel</catDesc></category>
                            <category xml:id="biomarker"><catDesc>biological measurements that can be tracked for analysis</catDesc></category>
                        </category>
                        <category xml:id="art"><catDesc>biology and physiology</catDesc>
                            <category xml:id="imaginarymachines"><catDesc>function, sketches, drawings of imaginary machines</catDesc></category>
                            <category xml:id="handdrawn"><catDesc>illustrations or sketches that are handdrawn</catDesc></category>
                            <category xml:id="detail"><catDesc>specific detailed attention, such as a diagram</catDesc></category>
                        </category>
                        <category xml:id="elements"><catDesc>journalmarkers</catDesc>                                                                                            
